Class Semantics.ReadingState

    Enclosing interface:
    Semantics

    public static class Semantics.ReadingState
extends Semantics.MappingState
    This class implements the possible state for a semantic reading process.

    In particular, this class manages the base state types (see Semantics.MappingState) and writing state states: More in details, this class extend Semantics.MappingState by adding to more states: ABSENT and SUCCESS.

    Thus, possible states for a Semantics.readSemantics() Array3D.SemanticMap.readSemantics( Semantics.Descriptor) processes are:

    • Semantics.MappingState.ERROR: implemented in Semantics.MappingState,
    • Semantics.MappingState.INCONSISTENT: implemented in Semantics.MappingState,
    • Semantics.MappingState.NOT_CHANGED: implemented in Semantics.MappingState,
    • ABSENT: reading failure, since not data were available in the semantic description,
    • SUCCESS: reading success, java representation has been up to dated.

    REMARK: extending classes must have static state fields assigned to inter values bigger than SUCCESS.

      • combineResults

        public static Semantics.ReadingState combineResults(Semantics.ReadingState r1,
                                                    Semantics.ReadingState r2)
        Merges two reading states and generates an output feasible state.

        In particular, it returns:

        • Semantics.MappingState.INCONSISTENT: if at lest one state is in inconsistent state,
        • Semantics.MappingState.ERROR: if at least one state is in error state,
        • Semantics.MappingState.NOT_CHANGED: if both did not change nothing. If only one input parameter is in Semantics.MappingState.NOT_CHANGED state, it returns the other.
        • ABSENT: if at least one state is in absent state,
        • SUCCESS: if is not one of the case above.
        Parameters:
        r1 - the first reading state to merge.
        r2 - the second reading state to merge.
        Returns:
        a new reading state obtained from the combination of the input parameters.
